The paper proposes a method for separating different speaker properties from a two-speaker signal in embedding space, which involves deep learning techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.SD (Sound), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed approach based on speaker identification accuracy, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SI (Sound and Image Processing).
